body: 66 (return) [ The Royal Canal (_Nahar-Malcha_) might be successively restored, altered, divided, &c., (Cellarius, Geograph. Antiq. tom. ii. p. 453;) and these changes may serve to explain the seeming contradictions of antiquity. In the time of Julian, it must have fallen into the Euphrates _below_ Ctesiphon.]
